      • formatLatencyExceededToleranceMessage

        public static java.lang.String formatLatencyExceededToleranceMessage(StatisticalLatencyRequirement requirement,
                                                                     WorkDuration duration,
                                                                     double deviationFromMean,
                                                                     double mean,
                                                                     java.lang.String exceededToleranceMessage)

        Formats an alert which indicates that the duration of a monitored task has exceeded the permitted tolerance in comparison to the mean latency.

        This involves replacing the filters, given by the following constants, with actual values taken from the method parameter list.

        • StandardHandlerConstants.WORK_CATEGORY_TOKEN: Replaced with the return value of the category as taken from the requirement specified in the argument list.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.THREAD_ID_TOKEN: Replaced with the id of the thread under which the task was executed as obtained from duration identifier, and the identifier's threadId field.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.DEVIATION_TOKEN: Replaced with the deviation from the mean, as specified in the parameter list.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.MEAN_TOKEN: Replaced with the mean latency, as specified in the parameter list.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.TOLERANCE_LEVEL_TOKEN: Replaced with the tolerance level as taken from the requirement in the parameter list.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.DURATION_TOKEN: The actual duration of the operation as specified in the parameter list.
        Parameters:
        requirement - The requirement to which the alert relates.
        duration - The duration of the task being monitored.
        deviationFromMean - The deviation of the task's duration from the current observed average.
        mean - The current observed average duration.
        exceededToleranceMessage - The template message on which the pattern replacement is to be performed.
        Returns:
        A formatted alert message with all specified filters replaced with values taken from the parameter list.

      • formatTargetMissedMessage

        public static java.lang.String formatTargetMissedMessage(CappedLatencyRequirement requirement,
                                                         WorkDuration duration,
                                                         java.lang.String message)

        Formats an alert which indicates that the duration of a monitored task/ operation has exceeded a pre-specified cap. This involves replacing the filters, given by the following constants, with real values taken from the parameter list.

        • StandardHandlerConstants.WORK_CATEGORY_TOKEN: Replaced with the operation category as taken from the requirement specified in the parameter list.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.THREAD_ID_TOKEN: Replaced with the id of the thread under which the operation was executed. This is obtained from the threadId field, taken from identifier of the specified duration.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.EXPECTED_LATENCY_TOKEN: The cap which has been breached. This value is given by the expected latency of the specified requirement.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.DURATION_TOKEN: The actual duration of the operation as specified in the parameter list.
        Parameters:
        requirement - The requirement to which the alert relates.
        duration - The duration of the monitored task.
        message - The template from which the alert message is generated.
        Returns:
        A formatted alert message with all filters replaced with actual values taken from the parameter list.

      • formatWorkCategoryFailureMessage

        public static java.lang.String formatWorkCategoryFailureMessage(LatencyRequirement requirement,
                                                                WorkDuration duration,
                                                                java.lang.String message)

        Formats an alert which indicates that a monitored task terminated with an exception. This involves replacing the filters, given by the following constants, with values taken from the parameter list.

        • StandardHandlerConstants.WORK_CATEGORY_TOKEN: Replaced with the category to which the failed task relates. This is taken from the requirement specified in the parameter list.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.THREAD_ID_TOKEN: Replaced with the id of the thread under which the task was executed as obtained from the identifier of the specified duration.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.EXCEPTION_MESSAGE_TOKEN: The message taken from the exception encapsulated in the specified duration.
        • StandardHandlerConstants.EXCEPTION_STACKTRACE_TOKEN: The stack trace of the exception object WorkDuration.getError().
        Parameters:
        requirement - The requirement to which the alert relates.
        duration - The duration of the monitored task.
        message - The template from which the message is built.
        Returns:
        A formatted message with all filters replaced with values taken from the parameter list.
